<P N="37">XXXVII. I HAVE long ago done
what you &s;o often exhort me to do, dili|gently
read and con&s;idered the &s;everal ac|counts
of this Doctrine given by the great
Author in different parts of his writings: and
upon the whole I could never make it out
to be con&s;i&s;tent and intelligible. I was
even led to &s;ay, "that one would be in|clined
to think, He was him&s;elf &s;u&s;pi|cious
of the ju&s;tne&s;s of his own demon|&s;trations:
